alerts.title: Special Weather Statement
alerts.description:
...Light snow still locally heavy in and around Detroit...
Light snow will continue through mid-afternoon at rates generally
less than one half inch for hour. Lake effect snow that has
produced locally heavy snow in the Detroit Metro and Ann Arbor
areas this morning has begun to diminish in intensity.
Nonetheless, occasional upticks in intensity will still be
possible as easterly wind moves across Lake Erie. Up to 1 inch
per hour snowfall rates possible into early afternoon on a
localized basis.

alerts.title: Winter Weather Advisory
alerts.description:
...Accumulating Snow To Impact Southeast Michigan Through This
Evening...
...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 PM EDT THIS
EVENING...
HAZARDOUS WEATHER...
* Light snow will continue into the evening hours.
* Localized, heavier bursts of snow will be possible today as
narrow lake effect bands move off Lake Erie.
* Widespread 2 to 5 inches is expected across the area with the
highest amounts of 5 inches generally along and south of the
I-696 corridor and east of US 23.
* Any heavier bursts could produce a very localized higher
accumulation, potentially upwards of 6 inches.
IMPACTS...
* Roadways will become snow covered and slippery through this
evening, affecting the evening commute.
* Heavier bursts of snow will reduce visibilities to one-quarter
of a mile at times.
